=== Etymology ===
From French ''cité'' which comes from the Latin ''civitas'' meaning "an organized community" a "a civilized place".

== [[noun]] ==
#a large settlement, bigger than a town. (The plural is ''cities''). In Europe a city is a place that had succeeded to obtain the right to build a [[city wall]], a [[belfort]], etc... from the impoverishing [[nobility]].

